Macon R-1 Middle School 702 N. Missouri St., Macon, MO
September 3 at 3:48 PM ·

MMS Students and Parents,

First of all, thank you for patience and understanding as we made the switch from in-person to online learning for our 6th grade students late yesterday.

Today Macon R-1 has been working closely with the Macon County Health Department to identify students and staff members that have been in close contact with the individual that produced the positive test. Individuals deemed to be close contacts will be notified by the Macon County Health Department and advised on how they should proceed.

Further contact tracing will continue over the next couple of days as the results of the pending tests are made known. Currently, the plan is to keep the 6th graders at home again tomorrow (9/4). Please continue to check your email and our social media sites for any updated information.

Sincerely,

Bruce Weimer
Macon Middle School Principal

Macon R-I Elementary Art
August 28 at 10:56 PM ·

The “B” classes (KB, 1B, 2B, 3B, 4B, and 5B had a busy week during their first art week this year) each of the above classes had art for 5 days in a row (the equivalent of 5 weeks of normal art instruction) to help with social distancing efforts. The other 4 sections of each grade will each have their turn as they cycle through over the next 4 weeks.

Here are some highlights of some of this weeks creative adventures together. Looking forward to the “C’s” next week. “C” kids please plan to wear clothes you can create art in this coming week, or bring a paint shirt with you to art. 🎨🎨🎨 especially 1C and 3C as you will paint atleast 1-2 of your art days this rotation.

See you next week!

The Home Press
July 1 at 9:28 PM ·

MACON, MO -- On June 30th the Macon Tiger Junior Varsity baseball team took on the Fulton Hornets for a doubleheader in Macon. The Tigers defeated the Hornets both games. As of this post, this was their only home game of the summer. Their next scheduled game is Tuesday (July 7th) at 3:30 p.m. in Harrisburg. The Varsity team will play shortly after.

Post and pictures by Reporter Benjamin Nelson

Macon Elementary
June 19 at 11:59 AM ·

MACON R-1
KINDERGARTEN SCREENING
JULY 2, 2020 11:00-7:00
https://signup.com/go/daNgBAO

A child must turn five before August 1, 2020 to be enrolled in kindergarten for the 2020-2021 school year.

If you have not already done so please submit the following items prior to your appointment via email (scans or pictures accepted) to kheaton@macon.k12.mo.us or fax 660-395-6150:
Child’s Legal Birth Certificate (or other legal documentation with child’s name)
Social Security Number (optional)
Immunization Records (required)
Proof of Residency (ie: recent utility bill)

Click this link to sign up https://signup.com/go/daNgBAO

Please contact kheaton@macon.k12.mo.us if your child will be attending Kindergarten at Macon Elementary in the fall but you are unable to bring them for a screening appointment on Thursday, July 2nd.

It’s virtual art show time! I’d love to make a slide show of student work to showcase our kids work on our school page. This could be a picture of the online challenge we did online here, a picture of a work they did in class before the stay at home order, or even something of their own creation just because.

If you’d like your student to be featured in our show, please submit the following to either this post or to my email

Hmallett@macon.k12.mo.us

Please include a picture, student name, title of artwork. (Optional: a short 1-3 sentences about the work. Could be an interesting fact, how they made it, why they chose it for the show etc.)

please send by Friday May 15th so I can put it together over the weekend.

Tigerettes Summer Basketball Camp
The 2020 Tigerettes Summer Basketball Camp will take place June 29-July 1. If your child is planning on attending, please register by completing the Google Form at the following link by May 20th. Session 1(4-6th grades) will be 12:30-2 and Session 2 (7th-8th grades) will be 2:00-3:30.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfrmI1Tq9oa2ymiF3tdaqbQuVKf0smZpwoN_z6AwhEJ8zCjIg/viewform?usp=sf_link

The cost will be $25.00 per camper and will include a T-shirt. Please bring the payment on the day of the camp. If you are paying by check make them out to the Macon R-1 School District. If you have any questions please feel free to email me at rdriscoll@macon.k12.mo.us . I look forward to seeing everyone in the gym this summer.

2020 Tiger All Level Football Camps
The Macon Tiger football program would like to invite you to attend the Tiger Football Camps. We are excited to develop a relationship and begin to work on the fundamentals of Tiger Football. The fee is $25.00 and your child will experience the same drills, learn the same terminology, and run the same plays as our High School program. It’s a great day to be a Tiger!
HS Team Camps: Week 1- July 13-17, 6-8:30 PM
Week 2 July 20-24, 7-10 AM

MS Team Camp (7th & 8th): July 21-23 10 AM- Noon

Youth Football Team Camp (3rd-6th): July 21-23 6-8 PM

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdVxdMDlu0hRssK3oHOL9CItE-gX745-oFseO0WsrfVeyDnFw/viewform?vc=0&c=0&w=1

Thanks,
Jameson Allen
Macon High School

Missouri Department of Elementary and Secondary Education
May 1 at 7:00 AM ·

Today, we celebrate "School Lunch Hero Day!" Between preparing healthy food, adhering to strict nutrition standards, navigating student food allergies, and offering service with a smile, Missouri nutrition professionals have a lot on their plate on a “normal” day. Extended building closures during COVID-19 required our food service professionals to quickly be innovative and creative to develop ways to continue feeding the Missouri students who rely on school breakfast and lunch each day.

Join us in recognizing these important team members today!

Macon R-I Elementary Art
April 29 at 2:48 PM ·

Here is our next art challenge fun for all ages, even adults! Choose a famous painting to recreate. These are good options I found online, but there are SO many. If you’re browsing lot’s of famous paintings, do so WITH parent supervision please. Be creative and have FUN!

1. Choose your artwork. Can screenshot an image you find online. A simple google search of famous paintings will give you lots of options. Or even a gallery of a museum site would work too.
2. Get dressed up and gather props
3. Have someone take your photo
4. Post to Facebook and share below.
(Can even use an app like pic collage to put the original pic with your created picture... and bonus points if you add the title/artist)

here are some resources/ideas about the challenge:

https://www.thisiscolossal.com/2020/04/covid-19-getty-recreations/

http://blogs.getty.edu/iris/getty-artworks-recreated-with-household-items-by-creative-geniuses-the-world-over/

Challenge #20 earth art! Andy Goldsworthy Is an amazing British sculpting artist. He is known for how he rearranges nature to create amazing works of art. Don’t forget to photograph your work and post below to share. Happy creating￼!

shared_text:
Macon Area Career and Technical Education Center
April 14 at 2:29 PM ·

Even though school is out, students involved in leadership organizations continue to work behind the scenes to prepare for next year.
Jasmine Stewart, Macon Senior, is a State Officer for Region III FCCLA next year. She is pictured doing her interview with the Department of Education as she runs for state President. Normally, this would take place at the state conference in front of 8000 members from across the state. This is just an example of how our amazing students are adapting to the changes thrown at them and making the best of the situation. Good Luck, Jasmine!
